		title: "Autonomous Helicopter Control",
		slot: 3,
		description: "<p>Reinforcement learning is a type of machine learning wherein intelligent agents learn optimal control policies by interacting with their environment.  It is useful for robot control, system optimization, game playing, information retrieval, etc.  In this talk, I give a brief introduction to the fundamental challenges of reinforcement learning, with particular emphasis on the dilemma between exploration and exploitation.  As a case study, I describe helicopter hovering, a benchmark challenge problem used in recent years in the international Reinforcement Learning Competitions.  I also describe the neuroevolutionary solution we developed that won the 2008 competition, as well as extensions developed for the 2009 competition and beyond that tackle the unique challenges of safe exploration in this high-risk domain.</p>",
