		title: "Agent Based AI in Games",
		slot: 7,
		description: "<p>The behavior of non-player characters (NPCs) in game environments is partly controlled by decision making logic implemented using Artificial Intelligence (AI) techniques. Whereas AI in other application fields is typically concerned with optimal decisions and expert behavior, its role in games is to entertain the player. Because of this, there is a bigger emphasis on believability, understandability and “perceived fairness” of the NPCs behavior. The talk presents various algorithms and tricks used in creating game play and shows that AI techniques originally created to achieve optimal decisions can be tailored to create fun.</p>",
